  "prompt": "What is voltage regulation formula?",
  "response": "The voltage regulation formula depends on the specific context, but here are two common formulas:\n\n1. For Transformers:\nVoltage Regulation % = [(No-load voltage - Full-load voltage) / Full-load voltage] \u00d7 100%\n\n2. For Power Systems/Generators:\nVoltage Regulation % = [(No-load voltage - Full-load voltage) / Full-load voltage] \u00d7 100%\n\nKey points:\n- Indicates how much voltage changes between no-load and full-load conditions\n- Lower percentage means better voltage stability\n- Typically expressed as a percentage\n- Calculated by comparing no-load and full-load voltages\n- Helps assess voltage quality and system performance\n\nThe specific formula might vary slightly depending on the specific electrical system or component being analyzed.\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any part of the voltage regulation formula?",
